in POSIX, BRE requires () and {} be designated \(\), \{\}, where as ERE does
not, BRE has no ?+| metacharacter.

ERE:

^
.
[]
[^]
$
()
\n match subexpression, n belongs to 1-9
*
{m,n}
?
+
|

POSIX supports only [:..:] style character class:

[:alnum:]
[:word:]
[:alpha:]
[:blank:]
[:cntrl:]
[:digit:]
[:graph:]
[:lower:]
[:print:]
[:punct:]
[:space:]
[:upper:]
[:xdigit:]

PCRE:
(?=..) look ahead
(?!..)
(?<=..) look behind
(?<!..)
